    "latest_plan": "## 1. Executive Summary\nA React login page for a Formula racing car website featuring images.\n\n## 2. Functional Requirements\n- User can enter username and password.\n- Login form should validate input.\n- On successful login, redirect to the dashboard.\n- Display error messages for invalid credentials.\n\n## 3. Non-Functional Requirements\n- Responsive design for mobile and desktop.\n- Fast load times under 1 second.\n- Secure authentication mechanism.\n- Error messages should be user-friendly.\n\n## 4. User Stories\n1. As a visitor, I want to see images of Formula racing cars so that I am interested in the website.\n2. As a visitor, I want to log in using my credentials so that I can access the dashboard.\n3. As a visitor, I want to receive error messages if my login fails so that I can correct my input.\n\n## 5. Acceptance Criteria\n1. Given a user visits the login page, When they enter valid credentials and submit, Then they should be redirected to the dashboard.\n2. Given a user visits the login page, When they enter invalid credentials and submit, Then they should see an error message.\n\n## 6. Assumptions\n- The website already has a backend service for authentication.\n- The images are hosted on a CDN or within the project's static files.\n- The dashboard URL is known.\n\n## 7. Constraints\n- Must use React for the frontend.\n- Authentication must be handled by an existing backend service.\n- No new database setup required.\n\n## 8. Domain Detection\nE-Commerce - The website features images, suggesting it may sell Formula racing car merchandise or related products.\n\n## 9. Recommended Tech Stack\n- Frontend: React\n- Backend: Not set (assumed to be handled by existing service)\n- Database: Not set (not required for this task)\n- Auth: Existing backend service\n- Infra/Hosting: Not specified\n\n```json\n{\n  \"project_name\": \"Formula Racing Car Website Login Page\",\n  \"domain\": \"E-Commerce\",\n  \"executive_summary\": \"A React login page for a Formula racing car website featuring images.\",\n  \"functional_requirements\": [\n    \"User can enter username and password.\",\n    \"Login form should validate input.\",\n    \"On successful login, redirect to the dashboard.\",\n    \"Display error messages for invalid credentials.\"\n  ],\n  \"non_functional_requirements\": [\n    \"Responsive design for mobile and desktop.\",\n    \"Fast load times under 1 second.\",\n    \"Secure authentication mechanism.\",\n    \"Error messages should be user-friendly.\"\n  ],\n  \"user_stories\": [\n    \"As a visitor, I want to see images of Formula racing cars so that I am interested in the website.\",\n    \"As a visitor, I want to log in using my credentials so that I can access the dashboard.\",\n    \"As a visitor, I want to receive error messages if my login fails so that I can correct my input.\"\n  ],\n  \"assumptions\": [\n    \"The website already has a backend service for authentication.\",\n    \"The images are hosted on a CDN or within the project's static files.\",\n    \"The dashboard URL is known.\"\n  ],\n  \"constraints\": [\n    \"Must use React for the frontend.\",\n    \"Authentication must be handled by an existing backend service.\",\n    \"No new database setup required.\"\n  ],\n  \"tech_stack\": {\n    \"frontend\": \"React\",\n    \"backend\": \"Not set (assumed to be handled by existing service)\",\n    \"database\": \"Not set (not required for this task)\",\n    \"auth\": \"Existing backend service\",\n    \"infra\": \"Not specified\"\n  }\n}\n```",
    "latest_architecture": "## 10. High-Level Architecture\n**Architecture Style:** Modular Monolith  \n**Components/Services:**\n- **Frontend:** React application for login page and dashboard.\n- **Backend:** Authentication service (assumed existing).\n- **Static Files:** Hosting images on a CDN or within the project.\n\n**Communication:** Client -> API -> Auth Service -> Redirect to Dashboard\n\n## 11. Database Schema\nNo database required for this task.\n\n## 12. API Specifications\n```plaintext\nPOST /api/login \u2014 Validate user credentials and return token.\n```\n\n## 13. Folder Structure\n```plaintext\nfrontend/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 public/\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 images/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 src/\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 components/\n\u2502   \u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 LoginForm.js\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 App.js\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 index.js\n\nbackend/\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 auth/\n    \u2514\u2500\u2500 routes.js\n```\n\n## 14. Development Roadmap\n```plaintext\nM0 Setup \u2014 Install dependencies and configure project.\nM1 Core Backend \u2014 Implement authentication API.\nM2 Frontend \u2014 Create login page and handle redirects.\nM3 Integration \u2014 Integrate frontend with backend.\nM4 Launch \u2014 Deploy the application.\n```\n\n## 15. Task Breakdown\n```plaintext\n1. Set up React environment (Frontend)\n2. Create LoginForm component (Frontend)\n3. Implement authentication API (Backend)\n4. Configure routes for authentication (Backend)\n5. Integrate frontend with backend (Frontend)\n6. Test login functionality (Testing)\n7. Deploy application to server (Deployment)\n```\n\n## 16. Dependency Graph\n```plaintext\nfrontend depends_on: backend, auth service\nbackend depends_on: auth service\n```\n\n## 17. Risk Analysis\n```plaintext\nRisk \u2014 Severity (Low/Medium/High) \u2014 Mitigation\nAuthentication security \u2014 Medium \u2014 Use existing secure service.\nNetwork latency \u2014 Low \u2014 Optimize CDN usage.\n```\n\n## 18. Cost & Resource Estimation\n- **Team Size:** 2 developers (Frontend, Backend)\n- **Infra Cost:** $50/month for managed hosting and CDN\n\n## 19. Testing Strategy\n```plaintext\n- Unit tests for LoginForm component.\n- Integration tests for authentication API.\n- End-to-end testing for login flow.\n```\n\n## 20. Deployment Strategy\n```plaintext\n- CI/CD pipeline using GitHub Actions.\n- Dev, Staging, and Prod environments.\n- Use managed hosting service.\n- Rollback plan in place.\n```\n\n```json\n{\n  \"architecture_style\": \"Modular Monolith\",\n  \"components\": [\"Frontend\", \"Backend\", \"Static Files\"],\n  \"database_schema\": [],\n  \"api_endpoints\": [{\"method\": \"POST\", \"path\": \"/api/login\", \"purpose\": \"Validate user credentials and return token.\"}],\n  \"folder_structure\": {\"frontend\": [\"public/images/\", \"src/components/LoginForm.js\", \"src/App.js\", \"src/index.js\"], \"backend\": [\"auth/routes.js\"]},\n  \"roadmap\": [{\"milestone\": \"M0 Setup\", \"goal\": \"Install dependencies and configure project.\"}, {\"milestone\": \"M1 Core Backend\", \"goal\": \"Implement authentication API.\"}, {\"milestone\": \"M2 Frontend\", \"goal\": \"Create login page and handle redirects.\"}, {\"milestone\": \"M3 Integration\", \"goal\": \"Integrate frontend with backend.\"}, {\"milestone\": \"M4 Launch\", \"goal\": \"Deploy the application.\"}],\n  \"tasks\": [{\"task\": \"Set up React environment (Frontend)\", \"agent\": \"Frontend\"}, {\"task\": \"Create LoginForm component (Frontend)\", \"agent\": \"Frontend\"}, {\"task\": \"Implement authentication API (Backend)\", \"agent\": \"Backend\"}, {\"task\": \"Configure routes for authentication (Backend)\", \"agent\": \"Backend\"}, {\"task\": \"Integrate frontend with backend (Frontend)\", \"agent\": \"Frontend\"}, {\"task\": \"Test login functionality (Testing)\", \"agent\": \"Testing\"}, {\"task\": \"Deploy application to server (Deployment)\", \"agent\": \"Deployment\"}],\n  \"dependency_graph\": {\